         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 29/1/74. ¶  ¶ Just returned from an exploring trip to the snowy mountains, rev. and dear Sir, I find your kind letter of the 15. inst. ¶  I had the pleasure of corresponding with Mr James,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.01.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Branwhite Clarke</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.3608 Clarke papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">For a published version of this letter, see Moyal (2003), pp. 1006-7.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">29/1/74.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Just returned from an exploring trip to the snowy mountains, rev. and dear Sir, I find your kind letter of the 15. inst.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> I had the pleasure of corresponding with Mr James, who <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(so I understand) is gone again to Sydney, and became acquainted with his excellent son, spending several days with him on the Hume River.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">i.e. the upper Murray River, NSW.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am very sorry, that I missed Major Clarke,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">W. B. Clarke’s son, Mordaunt Clarke. See also M to W. B. Clarke, 25 April 1874.</p>
               </note> but I enquired at four leading Hotels (including Scotts) but could hear nothing of his abode. I will send to morrow to the Military Office, and should I learn that he is still here, I will do myself the honor of waiting on him.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have read your adresses<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">W. B. Clarke (1873), W. B. Clarke (1874).</p>
               </note> with great interest; they reflect, like all you do, much honor on your genius &amp; unabating assiduity. I wonder, whether through Major Warburton's Expedition or that of Giles<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Expeditions by P. Warburton and E. Giles, westwards from the Overland Telegraph Line.</p>
               </note> we shall at last learn, what became of poor Leichhardt's party.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I met lately Mr Nicholson's family, whose brother<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mark Nicholson, brother of Leichhardt’s close friend William Nicholson, had settled in Victoria.</p>
               </note> was so generous to Leichhardt.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When you meet Mrs Cobham,<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mary Cobham?</p>
               </note> — pray — give her my best regards.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Amidst the arrear work of the Department (if such in its helpless state it still can be called) I have but a few moments left to bid you a most cordial "adieu"</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
